  "lyrics": "I'm lost in this nostalgic memory Of me and my parents and free Lost in this nostalgic memory Oh, acting like it's so hard to be me Lost in this nostalgic memory Lost in the better parts of me Oh, tripping away in this nostalgic memory Trying to find a way out of the night Cause when I wasn't here I gave light to the night But now it's a fight because you can't see the wrong right Can't demand more things when it's good for you When it's hard you don't demand from the other You don't remember the things that got you here And letting go to the wrong fear Lost in this nostalgic memory And fear that you take with you as You act like you finally caught up and lost this time And it's easier to blame It's easier to say that you're not the same The same to anyone So I'm glad you took your little cop and ride with me Never trusted me, never really ever really wanted me Just wanted the correlate of the mouthpiece To say that you're society and you had something like that So amazing when you give free styles to you and you're mine They had no way, they didn't see They didn't help, they didn't alleviate I'm just a one single serving friend Away from hating everything you do Hating everything you always do for you Including me Lost in this nostalgic memory Now you're just hating everything that Holds you down Even though you held me all the way Until I gave you my heart And now you've thrown it away",
